SIMPLE: proprietary
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Proprietary
<hw>Pro*pri"e*ta*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Proprietaries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>proprietarius</ets>: cf. F. <ets>propri⟦eacute⟧taire</ets>. See
<er>Propriety</er>, and cf. <er>Proprietor</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A proprietor or owner; one who has exclusive title to a thing; one
who possesses, or holds the title to, a thing in his own right.</def>
<rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A body proprietors, taken collectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A monk who had reserved goods and
effects to himself, notwithstanding his renunciation of all at the time
of profession.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proprietary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Proprietary
<hw>Pro*pri"e*ta*ry</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>proprietarius</ets>.]</ety> <def>Belonging, or pertaining, to a
proprietor; considered as property; owned; <as>as, <ex>proprietary</ex>
medicine</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Proprietary articles</b></col>, <cd>manufactured articles
which some person or persons have exclusive right to make and sell.</cd>
<rj><au>U. S. Statutes.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proprietor</ent>⟦br⟧
